S. African Government to Start Own Newspaper, City Press Reports

-- B y   L a u r e n   v a n   d e r   W e s t h u i z e n
-- 
2011-03-27T15:05:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-27/s-african-government-to-start-own-newspaper-city-press-reports.html
The South African government will
start its own newspaper from next month, City Press  reported 
today, citing Jimmy Manyi, head of government communications.  The government’s bi-monthly magazine,  Vuk’uzenzele , will be
turned into a monthly newspaper with a print run of 1.7 million
to 2 million copies, City Press said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lauren van der Westhuizen at  at
 lvanderwesth@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net . 